    <stitle>ALLISON WT TRANSMISSION ELECTRONIC CONTROLS - DESCRIPTION - MODE BUTTON FUNCTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>MODE BUTTON FUNCTION</title>
        <para>All shift selectors have a MODE DISPLAY BUTTON (
            <hotlnk document="s08003_4.xml" xrefid="f0800305">Figure 5</hotlnk>). The button is used to activate special
            functions that have been programmed into the ECM or to perform system diagnostics when the vehicle is
            stopped. In a normal operating mode, the MODE status will be indicated on the digital display by lighting
            "MODE ON" when the function is selected.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
